.TH YTSTREAM "1" "December 2025" "ytstream 202208182138-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ytstream \- Open YouTube video in media player
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ytstream
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,URL\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ytstream
is a script for streaming YouTube videos directly in a media player without downloading. It extracts the video stream URL and opens it in the configured media player.
.PP
The script is useful for watching videos without storing them locally.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B ytstream https://youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID
Stream YouTube video in media player
.TP
.B ytstream "https://youtu.be/VIDEO_ID"
Stream using short URL
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/ytstream/settings.conf
User configuration file for ytstream preferences
